00:12:47.370 --> 00:12:49.560
directly ahead.

00:12:49.560 --> 00:12:52.260
Bill, you're on stage.

00:12:52.260 --> 00:12:55.070
So just a very, very soft focus.

00:12:55.070 --> 00:12:57.610
So you're not staring
at any one thing.

00:13:01.210 --> 00:13:05.170
You can see out of your
peripheral vision, either side,

00:13:05.170 --> 00:13:06.045
above, below.

00:13:11.410 --> 00:13:15.060
And just maintaining
that nice, soft focus.

00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:16.930
Just take a couple
big, deep breaths,

00:13:16.930 --> 00:13:20.180
breathing in through the nose,
and out through the mouth.

00:13:22.896 --> 00:13:25.020
So as you breathe in through
the nose, just a sense

00:13:25.020 --> 00:13:28.850
that you're taking in some
fresh air, feeling the chest,

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:31.360
the lungs expanding.

00:13:31.360 --> 00:13:33.710
And as you breathe
out through the mouth,

00:13:33.710 --> 00:13:39.100
just a sense of the body
softening a little bit.

00:13:39.100 --> 00:13:44.700
Just a couple more times,
breathing in through the nose,

00:13:44.700 --> 00:13:46.454
and then out through the mouth.

00:13:52.620 --> 00:13:57.390
And with the next exhalation,
just gently closing the eyes.

00:14:02.990 --> 00:14:05.220
And as soon as you
close the eyes,

00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:11.580
you're going to become more
aware of the other senses.

00:14:11.580 --> 00:14:15.860
To begin with, I'd like you
to become particularly aware

00:14:15.860 --> 00:14:18.140
of the feeling of touch.

00:14:18.140 --> 00:14:23.170
The weight of the body
is pressing on the chair.

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:30.130
The souls of the
feet on the floor.

00:14:37.810 --> 00:14:43.610
And the hands and the arms
just resting on the legs.

00:14:50.640 --> 00:14:52.710
Remember, even at the
beginning, just allowing

00:14:52.710 --> 00:14:55.120
thoughts to come and go.

00:14:55.120 --> 00:14:57.780
We're just shifting
the attention

00:14:57.780 --> 00:14:59.090
to those physical sensations.

00:15:02.140 --> 00:15:04.050
We're starting to notice
the space around us,

00:15:04.050 --> 00:15:05.000
noticing any sounds.

00:15:23.390 --> 00:15:25.370
Noticing any resistance
to any sense.

00:15:33.940 --> 00:15:36.970
And then just gently bringing
the attention back to the body.

00:15:43.690 --> 00:15:48.260
I'd just like you to gently
scan down through the body now.

00:15:48.260 --> 00:15:52.470
Starting at the top of the head,
take the next 30 seconds or so.

00:15:52.470 --> 00:15:57.215
Just to scan downwards,
noticing how the body feels.

00:16:00.900 --> 00:16:04.385
What feels comfortable,
or feels uncomfortable.

00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:31.080
And not thinking
about the feelings,

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:32.910
just noticing the
feelings as you

00:16:32.910 --> 00:16:35.575
continue to scan down
towards the toes.

00:16:59.060 --> 00:17:01.450
Before shifting the
attention to the breath,

00:17:01.450 --> 00:17:05.710
just take a moment, just to
be really clear in your mind

00:17:05.710 --> 00:17:09.480
why you're doing what
you're doing right now.

00:17:09.480 --> 00:17:11.569
Just a sentence in your mind.

00:17:11.569 --> 00:17:16.470
A sense of why you're
doing what you're doing.

00:17:24.119 --> 00:17:26.329
And then just letting that
go, bringing the attention

00:17:26.329 --> 00:17:29.270
to the breath.

00:17:29.270 --> 00:17:32.930
Now you may feel the
breath in your stomach,

00:17:32.930 --> 00:17:36.691
in your chest, diaphragm.

00:17:36.691 --> 00:17:38.190
If you can't feel
the breath at all,

00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:40.675
just gently place your
hand on your stomach.

00:17:52.040 --> 00:17:54.290
And just notice, what
does the breath feel like?

00:18:08.310 --> 00:18:09.360
Are the breaths long?

00:18:12.030 --> 00:18:12.530
Short?

00:18:25.230 --> 00:18:26.760
Is it breathing deep or shallow?

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:50.590
And just to help maintain
the focus on that sensation,

00:18:50.590 --> 00:18:52.210
if you like, you can
just gently start

00:18:52.210 --> 00:18:54.060
to count the breaths
as they pass.

00:18:54.060 --> 00:18:56.850
As you feel the rising
sensation, you count one.

00:18:59.980 --> 00:19:01.280
Following sensation, two.

00:19:03.980 --> 00:19:07.700
Three, then four, just
up to a count of 10.

00:19:10.410 --> 00:19:13.120
Just try that a couple
times for right now.

00:19:50.300 --> 00:19:52.250
Remember, allowing
thoughts to come and go.

00:19:52.250 --> 00:19:55.660
If you do get distracted,
as soon as you realize,

00:19:55.660 --> 00:19:58.400
just gently bring the
attention back again.

00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:03.200
A rising and falling sensation.

00:20:56.450 --> 00:21:04.445
And just for a moment now,
just letting go of any focus.

00:21:08.910 --> 00:21:13.480
Letting the mind
be completely free.

00:21:13.480 --> 00:21:15.830
So for 10, 15, 20
seconds, just let

00:21:15.830 --> 00:21:18.970
it do whatever it wants to do.

00:21:18.970 --> 00:21:21.470
Let it think, if
it wants to think.

00:21:48.640 --> 00:21:51.870
And then just gently bringing
the attention back once again

00:21:51.870 --> 00:21:53.690
to the body.

00:21:53.690 --> 00:21:58.540
Starting to notice the physical
sensations again, the weight

00:21:58.540 --> 00:22:10.900
of the body, body on the
chair, the feet on the floor,

00:22:10.900 --> 00:22:11.875
the weight of the arms.

00:22:16.770 --> 00:22:20.830
You starting to notice
the sounds again.

00:22:24.900 --> 00:22:35.470
As you just become more aware
of the space around you,

00:22:35.470 --> 00:22:38.600
and in your own time,
when you're ready,

00:22:38.600 --> 00:22:41.720
you can just gently
open your eyes again.

