01:18:56.960 --> 01:18:58.850
different kinds of practice.

01:18:58.850 --> 01:19:01.320
In other words, so you have
the skills and stuff that's

01:19:01.320 --> 01:19:03.240
coming from Headspace,
and then someone

01:19:03.240 --> 01:19:04.942
had attended a
[INAUDIBLE] retreat,

01:19:04.942 --> 01:19:05.900
was the particular one.

01:19:05.900 --> 01:19:08.880
So how can people combine
different practices

01:19:08.880 --> 01:19:10.190
from where they are?

01:19:10.190 --> 01:19:11.630
ANDY PUDDICOMBE: Did you
have any thoughts yourself

01:19:11.630 --> 01:19:12.980
that you'd like to share first?

01:19:12.980 --> 01:19:14.140
BILL DUANE: No, curious.

01:19:14.140 --> 01:19:15.890
ANDY PUDDICOMBE: OK.

01:19:15.890 --> 01:19:21.780
My only experience has been
that when-- it's important

01:19:21.780 --> 01:19:24.570
that we stay with a
particular practice

01:19:24.570 --> 01:19:27.960
for a defined period of time.

01:19:27.960 --> 01:19:30.210
It's OK to do lots of
different practices,

01:19:30.210 --> 01:19:32.790
but as much as possible,
we need to stay

01:19:32.790 --> 01:19:33.870
with a defined practice.

01:19:33.870 --> 01:19:36.680
And that can be as
little as 10 days.

01:19:36.680 --> 01:19:38.370
But the reason I say
that is, otherwise

01:19:38.370 --> 01:19:40.600
it can become a little
bit pick and and mix.

01:19:40.600 --> 01:19:42.370
And it's like you're
doing an exercise,

01:19:42.370 --> 01:19:44.240
and maybe it becomes difficult.

01:19:44.240 --> 01:19:46.310
So it's, oh, that exercise
really isn't for me.

01:19:46.310 --> 01:19:48.050
I'll do a different one.

01:19:48.050 --> 01:19:49.945
And then we get into
this thing, where

01:19:49.945 --> 01:19:51.570
we're always jumping around.

01:19:51.570 --> 01:19:53.110
And we don't really
get the benefit

01:19:53.110 --> 01:19:55.960
from actually staying
with that, and learning

01:19:55.960 --> 01:19:57.780
through that process.

01:19:57.780 --> 01:19:59.500
Because the difficulties
and obstacles,

01:19:59.500 --> 01:20:01.710
they are the learning process.

01:20:01.710 --> 01:20:08.700
So I would just encourage you
as much as possible-- Maybe you

01:20:08.700 --> 01:20:11.850
have your Headspace time
each day where you check in.

01:20:11.850 --> 01:20:14.520
And that's in a way
compartmentalized

01:20:14.520 --> 01:20:18.760
as an exercise, but you
feel the mindfulness

01:20:18.760 --> 01:20:20.900
feeds into your everyday life.

01:20:20.900 --> 01:20:23.420
And equally isn't so
different, actually,

01:20:23.420 --> 01:20:27.350
from the community sittings
that you might have.

01:20:27.350 --> 01:20:29.590
But definitely in
terms of techniques,

01:20:29.590 --> 01:20:32.339
I would try to stay with them.

01:20:32.339 --> 01:20:33.880
And that's why the
packs are designed

01:20:33.880 --> 01:20:36.320
as they are, for
10 days or 30 days,

01:20:36.320 --> 01:20:38.037
so that you do stay with that.

01:20:40.900 --> 01:20:43.467
BILL DUANE: The
next one is, I've

01:20:43.467 --> 01:20:45.550
been trying to use Headspace
for a few months now.

01:20:45.550 --> 01:20:47.350
I'm currently in
the 15 days series,

01:20:47.350 --> 01:20:50.170
but find myself spending a lot
