01:20:50.170 --> 01:20:52.610
Better to go back to the
beginning, or picking up

01:20:52.610 --> 01:20:53.410
where I left off?

01:20:53.410 --> 01:20:54.580
ANDY PUDDICOMBE: OK.

01:20:54.580 --> 01:20:56.788
This is a really good one,
because everyone falls off

01:20:56.788 --> 01:20:58.560
to the meditation wagon.

01:20:58.560 --> 01:21:00.600
It happens to us all.

01:21:00.600 --> 01:21:02.740
So how to get back on.

01:21:02.740 --> 01:21:05.410
General rule of thumb, for
me at least with the app

01:21:05.410 --> 01:21:10.070
is, if you've missed more
than a couple of days,

01:21:10.070 --> 01:21:13.480
I recommend going back to
the start of the series

01:21:13.480 --> 01:21:15.960
that you're on.

01:21:15.960 --> 01:21:20.410
I don't mean like on a 40-day
series, you go back to day one.

01:21:20.410 --> 01:21:22.760
It's split into 10-day chunks.

01:21:22.760 --> 01:21:25.390
So if you've missed
more than a few days,

01:21:25.390 --> 01:21:26.890
let's say for more
than five days,

01:21:26.890 --> 01:21:29.400
I would go back to
day one of that part.

01:21:29.400 --> 01:21:31.660
So you pick up the
sense of continuity,

01:21:31.660 --> 01:21:34.340
the sense of teaching
that goes along with it.

01:21:34.340 --> 01:21:37.070
If you've missed more
than a couple of weeks,

01:21:37.070 --> 01:21:40.060
so we go back to the start,
day one, of that series.

01:21:40.060 --> 01:21:41.830
And if you've had a
really long time out,

01:21:41.830 --> 01:21:44.650
just to ease yourself back
in, go back to Take 10.

01:21:44.650 --> 01:21:48.630
As Bill said earlier, there
is no regression here.

01:21:48.630 --> 01:21:52.000
Going back to the start doesn't
mean you're going backwards.

01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:54.810
It just means that you're
finding what works best for you

01:21:54.810 --> 01:21:56.350
at that particular time.

01:21:56.350 --> 01:21:58.800
So don't be shy
about going back.

01:21:58.800 --> 01:22:01.910
And I've met some
people who they've

01:22:01.910 --> 01:22:04.480
been doing the Headspace
app for a couple of years,

01:22:04.480 --> 01:22:06.600
and I met some just
recently, and they said,

01:22:06.600 --> 01:22:08.301
oh I'm still on Take 20.

01:22:08.301 --> 01:22:10.050
And I said, oh, do you
miss a lot of days?

01:22:10.050 --> 01:22:12.196
They're like, no,
never missed a day.

01:22:12.196 --> 01:22:14.320
So I was doing the math,
and my math is really bad,

01:22:14.320 --> 01:22:15.236
but I'm like, hang on.

01:22:15.236 --> 01:22:18.130
That's 45 days, two years--
And she said, oh, I just

01:22:18.130 --> 01:22:21.810
didn't want to move on until
I'd absolutely perfected it.

01:22:21.810 --> 01:22:26.330
So each to their own.

01:22:26.330 --> 01:22:29.289
BILL DUANE: So to wrap up--
